-- Bayer, Galp Energia, K+S, Tesco: European Equity Preview
-- B y   J o s e p h   C i o l l i
-- 2012-05-09T04:00:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-08/bayer-galp-energia-k-s-tesco-european-equity-preview.html
The following companies’ shares may
have unusual moves in  European (SXXP)  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses.  The Stoxx  Europe  600 Index fell 1.7 percent to 250.58. The
 Stoxx 50 Index (SX5P)  decreased 1.5 percent to 2,350.90. The  Euro Stoxx
50 Index (SX5E) , a benchmark measure for nations using the euro, lost
2.1 percent to 2,236.11.  Bayer AG (BAYN)  : The largest German drugmaker plans to
sell its diabetes measurement devices business, the Financial
Times Deutschland reported, citing unidentified people with
knowledge of the prospective sale. The shares decreased 1.6
percent to 51.33 euros.  Galp Energia SGPS SA (GALP)  : Portugal’s biggest oil
producer agreed to buy  Eni SpA (ENI) ’s stakes in Portuguese
natural gas distribution companies Setgas and Lusitaniagas for
40.5 million euros ($52.7 million). Galp dropped 1.6 percent to
11.01 euros, while Eni fell 0.6 percent to 16.52 euros.  K+S AG (SDF)  : Europe’s biggest potash distributor agreed
to sell its nitrogen fertilizer distribution unit to OAO
EuroChem in a transaction that values the business at about 140
million euros. The shares sank 1.3 percent to 36.19 euros.  Tesco Plc (TSCO)  : The U.K. supermarket operator will
manage its 6 billion-pound ($9.7 billion) British pension plan
in order to boost returns and reduce dependence on consultants,
Reuters reported. The shares rose 1.3 percent to 323.45 pence.  To contact the reporter on this story:
